TextChange: Today's youth simply read a headline and take it for truth.  Media puts out stories for clicks.  Real journalism has faded.  Reality has faded.  What is left is garbage.  Everything is at extremes.  The left view the right as neo-nazi extremists.  The right view the left as USSR marxists.  The majority of people are centrists and may lean left or right, but the vast majority are aligned far more with the majority of society than they may believe.  Stories are perpetuated to such an extent in the echo chamber that people live in, that they begin to almost actually appear to be fact.  Hear a random statement online such as the conservative justices on supreme court have perjured themselves during confirmations.  Then the story is told, again and again, until everywhere everyone looks, it is being stated as a fact.  Most people who wish it was true, believe it to be true.  Very few verify, and before long, its just an accepted fact, regardless of the veracity of the statement.  =>
